Angell,<br><br>
In the units in which I served in Vietnam from May 1969 to June 1970, the 1/7 Artillery with the 1st Div. and the 2/77 Artillery with the 25th Div., color was NEVER an issue with anyone. I do not recall anyone ever even hinting about it. What was foremost in our minds was doing what we had to do to the best of our ability, staying alive, and helping others to stay alive, too.<br><br>
In Basic Training at Ft. Leonard Wood, MO, and in Advanced Individual Training at Ft. Sill, OK, I saw no problems of color either.<br><br>
Although I do hear anecdotal stories once and a while, I saw nothing to give them credibility.
